details:
The Strategies on Evidence and Outcomes Workgroup (SEOW) will conduct a public meeting to discuss benefit design considerations and other potential issues for the 2012-2013 plan year. 

***********
Parking at the Dept. of Administrative Services General Services Building:
Limited metered parking is available on Ferry Street, nearby streets and in the surface lot at the corner of Ferry and 13th streets. Full- and half-day permits ($3 or $6) are available for the rooftop only of the Ferry St. parking structure.  Permits can be purchased at the Parking Office, 1225 Ferry St SE, 1st  floor. The parking structure is located directly across the street from the meeting location.

***************************

The meeting location is accessible to persons with disabilities. A request for an interpreter for the hearing impaired or for other accommodations for persons with disabilities should be made at least 48 hours before the meeting to Rose Mann at 503-378-4606.

details: The OEBB/PEBB INNOVATION WORKGROUP will meet in public session.

**Executive Session: No admittance unless stated below. Thank you.

The executive session is being held pursuant to ORS 192.660(2)(f), which allows a governing body to hold an executive session to consider information or records that are exempt by law from public inspection. In compliance with ORS 192.660(6), no decisions will be made during this meeting.

Representatives of the news media, OEBB staff and individuals specifically invited to participate are allowed to attend this executive session. Representatives of the news media are specifically directed not to report on any of the deliberations during executive session, except to state the general subject of the session as previously announced.
